medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Patient presented with sharp right upper quadrant pain that started at 9 PM. The pain radiated to the epigastric region and right scapula. Associated symptoms included nausea and emesis of gastric contents. Denies fevers, chills, or changes in bladder or bowel habits. There was one similar episode in the past.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Hypertension, Asthma, Gastroesophageal Reflux Disease (GERD), Depression, Insomnia, Hyperlipidemia, and a history of right rotator cuff repair, right total knee replacement, two cesarean sections, and total hysterectomy.
